    "implementationPresent": false,

    "isRest": true,
    "isTest": false,
    "httpMethod": "PUT"
  }
]

Explanation:
- I extracted six API route entries from routes/orderRoutes.js corresponding to each distinct route+HTTP method pair declared with router.route(...).<method>(...).
- Path parameters were converted from Express-style ":id" to the required "{id}" form.
- The listed handlers are the controller functions invoked at the end of each middleware chain (addOrderItems, getOrders, getMyOrders, getOrderById, updateOrderToPaid, updateOrderToDelivered). These functions are imported at the top of the file from ../controllers/orderController.js, so implementationPresent is false for all entries.
- Each path is a literal string in this file (router.route('/...')), so isLiteral is true. None are derived from a framework naming convention; they are explicit route strings, so isDerivedFromConvention is false.
- isPrefix is false because each route is an exact route pattern as written here (they might be mounted under a parent path elsewhere, but within this file they're literal route patterns, not declared as a prefix-only usage).
- All entries are REST-style endpoints (CRUD-like operations on orders), so isRest is true. None appear intended for testing, so isTest is false.
- I also included the HTTP method for clarity (router chains different handlers per method). Middleware functions (protect, admin) were not listed as the primary handler since they are middleware; the final controller function is considered the handler that produces the response.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.
path.title: Path

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.
handler.title: Handler

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
handler_in_same_file.title: Handler In Same File

path_is_prefix.description: Whether the path string is a prefix rather than a full path.
path_is_prefix.title: Path Is Prefix

path_from_string_literal.description: Whether the path string is extracted from a literal string defined in the source code.
path_from_string_literal.title: Path From String Literal

path_from_naming_convention.description: Whether the path string is derived from a naming convention supported by the framework.
path_from_naming_convention.title: Path From Naming Convention

is_restful_api.description: Whether the API entry is for a RESTful API, rather than other types of APIs.
is_restful_api.title: Is Restful Api
